  "summary_markdown": "## What broke\n\nPressing ESC to dismiss an `action_required` notification banner while the TUI was in `ModeAwaitingLLM` caused the Bubble Tea event loop to hang for the full duration of a SQLite write. The freeze was most noticeable when a concurrent transaction already held the single database connection (`store.OpenMemory` sets `SetMaxOpenConns(1)`).\n\n## Root cause\n\n`routeKey` at `internal/tui/tui.go:1324` called `m.jobStore.MarkNotificationRead(ctx, n.ID)` synchronously, directly inside Bubble Tea's `Update()` method. Bubble Tea's event loop is single-threaded: `Update()` must return a new model and a `tea.Cmd`; any I/O inside `Update()` itself blocks the loop until the call returns. With one shared DB connection and a concurrent transaction in flight, the write queued behind the lock and the UI froze.\n\nThe pattern was already applied correctly in `handleInboxItemSelected` at `tui.go:1080-1085`, where `MarkNotificationRead` runs inside the returned `tea.Cmd` closure. The ESC snooze path at line 1324 was a parallel site that missed this.\n\n## Fix\n\nThe synchronous call was replaced with a deferred `tea.Cmd` closure that captures `n.ID` and `m.jobStore`, marks the notification read, and then fires the inbox re-poll — identical to the `handleInboxItemSelected` pattern. `Update()` now returns in microseconds regardless of SQLite contention.\n\n## Validation\n\nA purpose-built repro test (`TestTKT001_EscBannerDismiss_BlocksEventLoop`) held an exclusive write transaction on the single-connection pool for 200 ms while pressing ESC. The inverted assertion required `Update()` to block ≥ 150 ms (the bug condition). With the fix in place, `Update()` returned in **377 µs** — the assertion failed, confirming the fix. All 215 other tests in `internal/tui` remained green.\n\n## Next time\n\nWhenever a new ESC/Enter/dismiss handler is added to `routeKey`, the reviewer should verify that any store write is wrapped in a `tea.Cmd` closure. A lint note pointing from `routeKey` to the `handleInboxItemSelected` reference implementation would catch this class of bug at review time.",
