      "category": "api-patterns",
      "phase": "proposing",
      "severity": "critical",
      "description": "Bubble Tea's Update() is the event-loop tick and must never call blocking I/O directly. All DB, network, or filesystem operations must be returned as tea.Cmd closures so they run outside the Update frame. Any synchronous call inside Update() stalls the entire TUI for its duration — a hang that is silent and hard to attribute."
